From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0012/N] count_leading_zeros: add CountLeadingZerosImpl<T,16> for CHERI

`count_leading_zeros<T>` dispatches via `CountLeadingZerosImpl<T,
sizeof(T)>`, with specialisations for sizeof = 1, 2, 4, 8. On
CHERI/Morello purecap, callers reach the template with `sizeof(T) == 16`
(cap-sized) and trigger the undefined-template error.

Add a `<T, 16>` specialisation that strips capability metadata and
delegates to the 8-byte clz on the address. Guarded by
`__CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__` so non-CHERI builds don't see a stray
specialisation.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md §6 (patch 0012)

--- a/src/hotspot/share/utilities/count_leading_zeros.hpp
+++ b/src/hotspot/share/utilities/count_leading_zeros.hpp
@@ -213,4 +213,14 @@ template <typename T> struct CountLeadingZerosImpl<T, 8> {

 #endif

+#ifdef __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__
+// CHERI/Morello purecap: 16-byte capability storage. clz only meaningful on
+// the address bits; treat as uint64_t.
+template <typename T> struct CountLeadingZerosImpl<T, 16> {
+  static unsigned doit(T v) {
+    return CountLeadingZerosImpl<uint64_t, 8>::doit(static_cast<uint64_t>(static_cast<uintptr_t>(v)));
+  }
+};
+#endif // __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__
+
 #endif // SHARE_UTILITIES_COUNT_LEADING_ZEROS_HPP
